# Remember changes this agent makes

After **substantive** work (new files, refactors, feature/bugfix edits, config changes—not tiny typo-only fixes unless the user cares), **append** a short entry to **`.cursor/change-log.md`**.

**Entry format** (newest entries at the **top**, after the title block):

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — one-line summary
- What changed and why (2–4 bullets max). Mention key paths like `src/...` if helpful.
```

If **`change-log.md`** is missing, create it with this header:

```markdown
# Change log (agent)

Dated notes when Cursor agents modify this repo. Newest first.
```

**Do not log:** dependency installs alone, formatting-only churn, or read-only exploration.

Before larger tasks, **skim the latest section** of `change-log.md` so you don’t contradict recent decisions.
